This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and language modeling. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it involves acoustic modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model architecture and training method. Finally, it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing an end-to-end model for speech recognition.
